   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Envelope 2013: CCAC - Climate and Clean Air Coalition</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fast action to reduce short-lived climate pollutants (SLPs) can have a direct impact on global Warming, with the potential to reduce the Warming expected by 2050 by up to 0.5degrees C. The Climate and Clean Air he Climate and Clean Air Coalition is the first global effort to treat SLCPs as a collective challenge by catalysing new action and strengthen the work of existing efforts such as the Arctic Council, the Montreal Protocol, and the Global Methane Initiative (GMI). The Coalition will address SLCPs by raising awareness of SLCP impacts and mitigation strategies; enhancing and developing new national and regional actions by building capacity and mobilising support in developing countries; promoting best practices and showcasing successful efforts; and improving scientific understanding of short lived climate pollutant impacts and mitigation strategies.</narrative>
  </description>
